<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-01-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo
                                        City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-01-16"><hi rend="italic">January 16,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. “N.”]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state to the
                            Department that Mr. Férère, the minister of foreign relations, has not
                            yet replied to our note that Department instructed me to send, in regard
                            to the license tax.</p>
                        <p>Our merchants are being pressed to pay this unjust tax, and when they
                            refuse the Government refuses to permit them to take their merchandise
                            from the custom-house.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. F. Powell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>